992
00:54:24,411 --> 00:54:25,712
the first day we launched the game,

993
00:54:26,112 --> 00:54:27,734
people started to post on our forum

994
00:54:28,114 --> 00:54:29,635
to apologize to each other

995
00:54:29,716 --> 00:54:32,058
for not being able to play through the whole game

996
00:54:32,138 --> 00:54:33,039
because they had to leave.

997
00:54:33,399 --> 00:54:34,780
But they couldn't tell the other person,

998
00:54:34,820 --> 00:54:36,702
so they started to leave in post on our forum.

999
00:54:37,303 --> 00:54:39,965
And I can never imagine a Call of Duty player do that,

1000
00:54:40,005 --> 00:54:41,186
but they are the same person.

1001
00:54:41,847 --> 00:54:42,047
Right?

1002
00:54:42,607 --> 00:54:45,269
And so as you play the game,

1003
00:54:45,349 --> 00:54:49,291
you slowly build up your scarf and cape,

1004
00:54:49,491 --> 00:54:51,932
and you become one more veteran player.

1005
00:54:53,653 --> 00:54:56,295
And I have a bunch of fan art here,

1006
00:54:56,375 --> 00:54:58,997
because I think fan art is a great way

1007
00:54:59,037 --> 00:55:01,678
to see what the player remembered about your game.

1008
00:55:01,818 --> 00:55:04,660
And they usually would remember the most intense emotion,

1009
00:55:05,941 --> 00:55:08,962
and this is what they remembered.

1010
00:55:09,122 --> 00:55:10,863
They draw hearts at the end of the game.

1011
00:55:12,303 --> 00:55:17,327
They remember the awe and the sublime beauty of the world.

1012
00:55:17,847 --> 00:55:23,711
They remember being scared and afraid of the danger.

1013
00:55:23,731 --> 00:55:27,154
And they also remember struggling together with each other

1014
00:55:27,614 --> 00:55:30,416
and helping each other to push all the way to the end.

1015
00:55:32,536 --> 00:55:36,917
And so, before all these awards season,

1016
00:55:37,018 --> 00:55:38,818
I still question whether it's worth it

1017
00:55:39,498 --> 00:55:41,139
to push a game to its extreme.

1018
00:55:43,440 --> 00:55:47,421
Up to today, we have 896 emails from our fans

1019
00:55:47,461 --> 00:55:49,382
who tell us very personal stories

1020
00:55:49,822 --> 00:55:51,482
about how they interact with the game.

1021
00:55:52,183 --> 00:55:55,524
A while back at DICE, I've shared this letter.

1022
00:55:59,257 --> 00:55:59,957
I'm just going to read it.

1023
00:56:00,718 --> 00:56:02,659
Your game practically changed my life.

1024
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:04,821
It was the most fun I had with him

1025
00:56:05,241 --> 00:56:06,522
since he had been diagnosed.

1026
00:56:07,543 --> 00:56:09,024
My father passed in the spring of 2012,

1027
00:56:10,565 --> 00:56:12,467
only a few months after his diagnosis.

1028
00:56:13,368 --> 00:56:16,630
Weeks after his death, I could finally return myself

1029
00:56:16,670 --> 00:56:17,511
to play video games.

1030
00:56:18,231 --> 00:56:19,312
I tried to play Journey,

1031
00:56:19,833 --> 00:56:21,834
and I could barely get past the title screen

1032
00:56:21,874 --> 00:56:23,295
without breaking down into tears.

1033
00:56:23,976 --> 00:56:26,738
In my dad's and in my own experience with Journey,

1034
00:56:27,098 --> 00:56:27,859
it was about him.

1035
00:56:28,679 --> 00:56:30,400
and his journey to the ultimate end.

1036
00:56:31,121 --> 00:56:32,782
And I believe we encountered your game

1037
00:56:32,862 --> 00:56:34,242
at the most perfect time.

1038
00:56:34,903 --> 00:56:37,825
I want to thank you for the game that changed my life,

1039
00:56:38,225 --> 00:56:40,446
the game whose beauty bring tears to my eyes.

1040
00:56:41,126 --> 00:56:43,828
Journey is quite possible the best game I've ever played.

1041
00:56:44,468 --> 00:56:46,770
I continue to play it and always remembering

1042
00:56:47,190 --> 00:56:49,932
what joys it brought and the joy it continues to bring.

1043
00:56:50,972 --> 00:56:54,454
I'm Sophia, I'm 15, and your game changed my life for better.

1044
00:56:55,855 --> 00:56:56,976
And, and, and...

1045
00:57:07,151 --> 00:57:11,812
And seeing this letter, somehow it brought back to me about this fan art.

1046
00:57:12,592 --> 00:57:15,853
I think, you know, it is what life is about.

1047
00:57:16,133 --> 00:57:18,654
We are only here for such a short amount of time.

1048
00:57:19,154 --> 00:57:23,415
We happen to be all living in the same era, and let's help each other.

1049
00:57:23,835 --> 00:57:25,216
Let's make each other's life better.

1050
00:57:25,716 --> 00:57:30,797
And that's why I think, as a game developer, you know, that's the best thing we could do.

1051
00:57:30,917 --> 00:57:33,178
And that's why I love making games, you know.

1052
00:57:33,838 --> 00:57:35,558
And that's why, you know.

1053
00:57:37,131 --> 00:57:37,236
So.

